[[File:Tarasin_darksider_UP.png|thumb|right|250px|A [[Tarasin]] corrupted by the dark side of the Force.]]
'''Darksider''', also spelled '''dark-sider''', was a catch-all term for any [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-user]] who followed the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]]. While it primarily referred to the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] or [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]], it could also refer to the [[Prophets of the Dark Side]], the [[Nightsisters/Legends|Nightsisters]] of [[Dathomir/Legends|Dathomir]], the [[Sorcerers of Tund/Legends|Sorcerers of Tund]], or any other dark side followers and their organizatoins.

The Dark Side users, specifically the Dark Jedi, were fueled with hatred, obsession and desire for the material world, and accepting their physical bodies. This contrasted the orthodox [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi teaching]] who focused on their existence as luminous beings that transcend their "crude" material bodies.<ref name="The Dark Forces Saga">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20050526a|series=The Dark Forces Saga|text=Part 4: Of the Crudest Matter}}</ref>

After his resurrection, [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] formed the [[Dark Side Elite]], a specialized corps of seven Dark Jedi often referred to as Dark-siders.<ref name="DEII">''[[Star Wars: Dark Empire II]]''</ref>

